@startuml tmu_remote_climate_to_comfort_profile_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title TMU Remote Climate To Comfort Profile Signal Flow\n(TMU/HVAC -> BCM -> comfort profile / seat/sunroof commands)

participant "TMU / HVAC inputs" as ClimateCtx #F4F7FB
participant "BCM\ncomfort owner" as BCM #E8F7E8
participant "Seat / Sunroof /\nComfort bus" as ComfortBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / panels" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Remote Climate Inputs ==

ClimateCtx -> BCM : gTmuRemoteClimateReq\ngTmuServiceMode\ngHvacCabinSetTemp\ngHvacBlowerLevel\ngHvacAcOn\ngDriveState
BCM -> BCM : if manualMode == 0 and\nremoteClimateReq == 1 and\nserviceMode >= 1
BCM -> BCM : derive seatHeatLevel / seatVentLevel
BCM -> BCM : derive sunshadeCmd /\nsunroofPositionCmd / sunroofTiltCmd
note right of BCM
Representative derived commands
- SeatHeatLevel / SeatVentLevel
- SunroofPositionCmd / TiltCmd
- SunshadeCmd
end note

== Comfort Command Publish ==

BCM -> ComfortBus : frmSeatControlMsg
BCM -> ComfortBus : frmSunroofControlMsg
BCM -> BCM : if remote climate or seat comfort active\nthen comfortProfile = 3
BCM -> ComfortBus : frmBodyComfortStateMsg
note right of BCM
Representative comfort output
- ComfortProfile = 3 for remote climate / comfort assist
- ComfortStatus / ComfortError
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

ComfortBus -> Obs : comfort profile / seat / sunroof readback

note over ClimateCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. TMU/HVAC remote-climate context reaches BCM
2. BCM derives seat and sunroof comfort commands
3. BCM lifts ComfortProfile into remote-climate mode
4. Comfort buses and panels expose the resulting body-comfort state
end note

@enduml
